Henry Cuellar is a seasoned politician and dedicated public servant who has been serving the people of Texas for over two decades. Born on September 19, 1955, Cuellar has a long and impressive career in public service, having served in various positions at the local, state, and federal levels.

Cuellar began his political career in 1981 when he was elected to the Texas House of Representatives. He served in this position for 14 years before being elected as Texas Secretary of State in 2001. In this role, Cuellar worked to improve the state's election laws and oversaw the implementation of new voting technology.

In 2005, Cuellar was elected to the United States House of Representatives, where he has been serving ever since. He represents the 28th congressional district of Texas, which includes Laredo, his hometown. Cuellar is a member of the Democratic Party and has been a vocal advocate for issues such as healthcare, education, and border security.

Throughout his career, Cuellar has worked tirelessly to improve the lives of the people in his district and throughout Texas. He has been a strong supporter of legislation to expand access to healthcare, increase funding for education, and reform the criminal justice system.

Cuellar has also been a vocal advocate for comprehensive immigration reform, believing that a fair and humane immigration system is essential for the continued success of the United States. He has worked to secure funding for border security measures while also advocating for reforms to the country's immigration laws.

In addition to his work in Congress, Cuellar has also been actively involved in his community, serving on various boards and commissions and working with local organizations to address issues such as poverty, education, and healthcare. He is known for being a hands-on and accessible leader who is always willing to listen to the concerns of his constituents.

Henry Cuellar's commitment to public service and dedication to improving the lives of his constituents have earned him the respect and admiration of many. He continues to serve as a voice for the people of Texas in Congress, fighting for policies that benefit the residents of his district and the country as a whole.
